title: Urutora sakusen daiichigou
description: Ultraman is escorting his prisoner to its final destination. The prisoner escapes and heads toward Earth. As Ultraman follows in pursuit, he accidentally crashes into an Earth craft, injuring its pilot and altering both of their lives forever.

title: Shinryakusha o ute
description: The Balatans have come to Earth to make a new home, at the expense of Earth's inhabitants.

title: Katokutai shutsugeki seyo
description: An invisible monster that thrives on electricity begins destroying power plants in Japan.

title: Daibakuhatsu gobyoumae
description: A nuclear bomb has gone missing and winds up being stuck to a lizard-like monster. This monster is bent on ruining Fuji's vacation.

title: Miroganda no himitsu
description: A scientist finds a rare plant that is determined to destroy humanity.

title: Engan keibi meirei
description: The Science Patrol has to deal with the smuggler Diamond Kick and a cacao-eating monster from Brazil.

title: Barâji no akai ishi
description: The Science Patrol heads to Turkey to investigate tales of a village that has disappeared. What they find is a giant ant-like monster who is familiar with Ultraman.

title: Kaijuu muhou chitai
description: The Science Patrol is summoned to an island where a research team has been reported as missing. The rescue effort is hindered when it is revealed that the island is crawling with monsters.

title: Denkou sekka sakusen
description: A uranium-eating monster threatens a boys mountain camp, forcing the Science Patrol to attempt to lure the monster away from the kids.

title: Nazo no kyouyuu kichi
description: A mad scientist who loves monsters creates a monster of his own and hides it in a lake.

title: Uchuu kara kita abarenbou
description: A meteorite that falls to Earth gives anyone who controls it the power to make their thoughts become reality. A man who steals the meteorite wants to create a monster in order to control the world.

title: Miira no sakebi
description: Scientists uncover a 10,000 year old mummy, who is not as dead as it appears. The mummy also has an unexplained connection to a giant dragon.

title: Oiru SOS
description: A giant bat-like monster travels the planet eating the world's oil.

title: Shinjugai bouei shirei
description: A pearl-eating monster wreaks havoc on world pearl prices, much to Fuji's consternation.

title: Kyoufu no uchuusen
description: Mysterious space rays transform a child's two-dimensional drawing into a three-dimensional monster, who would rather sleep than fight.

title: Katokutai uchuu e
description: The Baltans abduct a spacecraft on its way to Venus in order to get revenge against Earth and Ultraman.

title: Mugen e no pasupôto
description: Mysterious space rocks spell trouble for the Science Patrol. When the rocks are stored together they combine to create a giant rock that can manipulate the fourth dimension.

title: Yuusei kara kita kyoudai
description: An alien arrives on Earth claiming to be the brother of humanity. While he claims that the Science Patrol does not have Earth's best interest in mind, Ultraman begins attacking Earth.

title: Akuma wa futatabi
description: An object that is unearthed at a construction site is initially believed to be a time capsule. Further investigation reveals that it is a prison for two dangerous monsters.

title: Kyoufu no rûto 87
description: A dragon statue that was designed by a boy comes to life when the boy is killed by a car. The dragon's mission is to protect children from the dangers of automobiles.

title: Fun'en toppa seyo
description: A monster terrorizes a mountain by emitting a poisonous gas. Luckily for the Science Patrol, the monster has a vulnerable spot on its back.

title: Chijou hakai kousaku
description: Survivors of an underground and ancient civilization come to the surface of Earth with the intent of taking control of Ultraman.

title: Kokyou wa chikyuu
description: An astronaut returns to Earth after being transformed into a monster. His goal is to exact revenge on the people of Earth.

title: Kaitei kagaku kichi
description: The Science Patrol inaugurates a new undersea base, but run into trouble when a monster disrupts the ceremony.

title: Kaisuisei Tsuifon
description: The shock wave from an approaching comet is expected to detonate a missing nuclear bomb. Unfortunately for the Science Patrol, the bomb is located inside one of three different monsters. The Science Patrol must dispatch the three monsters without allowing the nuclear bomb to detonate.

title: Kaijuu denka Zenpen
description: Scientists capture a monster in order to put in on display at the World's Fair. Their attempt fails and the monster is on the loose. After the monster begins tunneling underground, the Science Patrol must track its location so they can prevent it from harming nearby populated areas.

title: Kaijuu denka Kouhen
description: After the monster eludes both the Science Patrol and Ultraman, the threat to the population becomes even greater.

title: Ningen hyouhon 5 6
description: Ultraman's old foe Dada arrives on Earth and is collecting human specimens for their experiments.

title: Chitei e no chousen
description: After all of the gold in a mountain has disappeared it is revealed that a monster has been eating the precious metal.

title: Maboroshi no yukiyama
description: After a ski resort experiences some trouble, the Science Patrol investigates a mysterious girl and her rumored guardian monster.

title: Kitanowa dareda
description: A Science Patrol member from South America who was born in Japan makes a return visit. Bringing with him a sample of a man-eating plant.

title: Hateshinaki gyakushuu
description: A member of the Science Patrol is on vacation from India. Her vacation is cut short when a monster begins burning mountains and surrounding areas.

title: Kinjirareta kotoba
description: An alien comes to Earth seeking to take control of it. But the only way he can get it is if he has permission from a boy. When the boy refuses, the alien decides to attack.

title: Sora no okurimono
description: A monster falls from the sky and presents a peculiar problem for the Science Patrol. It's too heavy for the Patrol to deal with.

title: Kaijuu bochi
description: A monster is inadvertently brought to Earth from the monster graveyard. The Science Patrol attempts to return it back to where it belongs.

title: Utsuna! Arashi
description: A monster with the ability to blind it's victims, and the ability to become stronger after being attacked, begins wreaking havoc. Science Patrol member Arashi gets into trouble when he defies orders to leave the monster alone.

title: Chiisana eiyuu
description: The small monster Pygmon returns with a warning that a monster who can control other monsters is preparing an all-out attack against Earth.

title: Uchuusen kyuujo meirei
description: Members of a space station are blinded by a mysterious force on another planet. The Science Patrol is called in to investigate

title: Saraba Urutoraman
description: An alien invasion fleet arrives at Earth. While the Science Patrol deals with an infiltrator, Ultraman must confront the alien leader.
